# Design System Rules

This project is **Tailwind-first**. Default to utility classes on components; add custom CSS only when Tailwind cannot express the behavior.

## Styling approach (required)

1. **Tailwind utilities first** — layout, spacing, color, typography, borders, shadows, transitions, and responsive behavior go in `class` attributes.
2. **Theme tokens** — colors and spacing come from `src/styles/theme.css` (`@theme` + `--token-*`). Use semantic utilities, not hardcoded hex or raw `var(--color-*)` in components.
3. **Shared component classes sparingly** — only in `src/styles/global.css` `@layer components` when the same pattern is reused and awkward as utilities (e.g. `.surface`, `.service-card__cta` with RTL `::after`).
4. **Custom CSS last** — keyframes, `dialog::backdrop`, `prefers-reduced-motion`, JS-driven marquee distance, and pixel-perfect hero avatar positioning. Put shared keyframes in `src/styles/motion.css`; page-specific rules in `ComponentName.styles.astro` with `<style is:global>`.

Do **not** recreate removed files (`components.css`, `tokens.css`, `typography.css`, `links.css`, `utilities.css`).

## Theme & tokens (`src/styles/theme.css`)

- Runtime palette switches on `<html data-theme="dark|light">` via `--token-*` variables.
- `@theme` maps tokens to Tailwind utilities: `bg-bg`, `bg-surface`, `text-text`, `text-text-muted`, `border-border`, `text-primary`, `bg-hover`, `shadow-md`, etc.
- Layout width: `--container-max: 77.5rem` — use `max-w-[var(--container-max)]` on `Container.astro` (do not use `max-w-container`; it is not generated).
- Theme variants: `dark:` and `light:` (custom variants on `[data-theme]`). Example: theme toggle icons `hidden dark:inline-flex` / `hidden light:inline-flex`.
- Spacing scale: `--spacing-1` … `--spacing-8` → `p-4`, `gap-5`, `mt-4`, etc.

## Global CSS (`src/styles/global.css`)

Imports: `tailwindcss` → `theme.css` → `motion.css`.

- `@layer base` — resets, body `bg-bg text-text`, locale fonts.
- `@layer components` — `.surface`, `.icon`, and other small shared patterns built with `@apply`.

## Typography

- Use `Typography.astro` variants only: `headline`, `body1`, `body2`, `button`, `caption` (Tailwind inside the component).
- **English:** Raleway (`html[lang="en"]`).
- **Farsi:** Vazirmatn (`html[lang="fa"]`).

## Common patterns

| Need | Prefer |
|------|--------|
| Panel / card chrome | `surface` class or `rounded-md border border-border bg-surface` |
| Page width | `Container` (`max-w-[var(--container-max)]`) |
| Card hover | `transition-[border-color,box-shadow,transform] duration-200`, `before:bg-gradient-to-br`, `hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md` |
| Gradients | `bg-gradient-to-br` (never `bg-linear-to-br`) |
| Focus rings | `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary/50` |
| RTL arrow on CTA | `rtl:after:content-['←']` or `.service-card__cta` in global.css |

## When custom CSS is allowed

- `@keyframes` and animation names referenced from `@theme` (`--animate-*`)
- `prefers-reduced-motion` overrides (`motion.css`)
- Native `dialog::backdrop`
- Pseudo-elements tied to JS state (typewriter caret, marquee with `--marquee-distance`)
- Complex absolute positioning that is brittle as utilities (hero avatar — keep in `HeroSection.styles.astro`)

## MD3 & theme behavior

- Clear hierarchy, consistent spacing, accessible interactions.
- Dark mode default (`data-theme="dark"`); light via `[data-theme="light"]`.
- Theme toggle and language switch in `SiteToolbar` (fixed, top inline-end).

## Interactive UI

- `focus-visible` on all buttons and links.
- Modals: native `<dialog>` + `showModal()`; panel mostly Tailwind or `Popup.styles.astro`; backdrop in CSS only.
- Prefer `Container`, `Flex`, `Stack` before ad-hoc wrappers.
